Stricken language would be deleted from and underlined language would be added to present law.
Act 519 of the Regular Session
1 State of Arkansas As Engrossed: S3/5/25 H3/20/25
A Bill
2 95th General Assembly
3 Regular Session, 2025 SENATE BILL 324
4
5 By: Senator M. Johnson
6 By: Representative Brooks
7
For An Act To Be Entitled
8
9 AN ACT TO AMEND THE LAW CONCERNING THE MEMBERSHIP OF
10 A COUNTY PLANNING BOARD; AND FOR OTHER PURPOSES.
11
12
Subtitle
13
14 TO AMEND THE LAW CONCERNING THE
15 MEMBERSHIP OF A COUNTY PLANNING BOARD.
16
17 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF ARKANSAS:
18
19 SECTION 1. Arkansas Code § 14-17-203(a), concerning members of a
20 county planning board, is amended to read as follows:
21 (a)(1) With the approval of the majority of the members of the county
22 quorum court, the county judge of any county may create a county planning
23 board.
24 (2) The county planning board shall consist of not less than
25 five (5) members nor more than twelve (12) members appointed by the judge and
26 confirmed by the court county quorum court.
27 (3) At least one-third (⅓) of the members of the county planning
28 board shall not hold any other elective office or appointment, except
29 membership on a municipal or joint planning commission or a zoning board of
30 adjustment.
31 (4) A majority of the voting members of the county planning
32 board shall reside in an unincorporated area of the county.
33
